The paper deals with attacks on post-quantum public key cryptosystems, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of QC-LDPC and QC-MDPC codes suggests that the paper may also be relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and coding theory (cs.CC). The focus on specific decoding algorithms and the structure of the secret key suggests that the paper may also be relevant to cryptography (cs.CY) and software engineering (cs.SE).
